# Master Plan: Design Information Modelling (DIM)

This document serves as the single source of truth for the evolution of the 3D authoring environment in Standlo, transitioning from the legacy "Canvas" concept to the new **Design Information Modelling (DIM)** architecture. 

It merges the codebase-wide entity migration ([Canvas](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/design/page.tsx#3-6) -> [Design](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/schemas/design.ts#38-39)) with the advanced performance and aesthetic goals of the Data-Driven Rendering (v2.0) engine.

---

## Part 1: Domain Ubiquitous Language Migration ([Canvas](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/src/app/%5Blocale%5D/design/page.tsx#3-6) -> [Design](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Development/STANDLO/standlo.com/functions/src/schemas/design.ts#38-39))
*Goal: Align the codebase terminology with the new reality where a `type` field allows creating designs for anything (parts, assemblies), not just for "stands".*

### 1.1 Backend (`functions/src/`)
- Rename schema: `schemas/canvas.ts` -> `schemas/design.ts`
  - Update `CanvasSchema` -> `DesignSchema`.
  - Update `canvasType` -> `designType`.
- Rename Orchestrator: `orchestrator/canvas.ts` -> `orchestrator/design.ts`
  - Replace route parameters, `orchestratorCanvas` -> `orchestratorDesign`.
- Rename Choreography: `choreography/canvas.ts` -> `choreography/design.ts`
  - Update triggers: `onDocumentCreated("canvases/{designId}")` -> `...("designs/{designId}")`.
- Update the Policy Engine (`rbac/policyEngine.ts`) mapping the resource `canvas` to `design`.
- Update API Gateways (`gateways/choreography.ts`, `gateways/orchestrator.ts`) to hit `design` endpoints.

### 1.2 Admin App (`admin/`)
- Rename domain editor components:
  - `admin/app/pdm/stands/components/StandCanvasEditor.tsx` -> `StandDesignEditor.tsx`
  - `admin/app/pdm/bundles/components/BundleCanvasEditor.tsx` -> `BundleDesignEditor.tsx`
  - `admin/app/pdm/assemblies/components/AssemblyCanvasEditor.tsx` -> `AssemblyDesignEditor.tsx`
- Update any links or state targeting the entity within the PDM.

### 1.3 Frontend App (`src/`)
- **Crucial Note:** We strictly rename Domain Entities and NOT the rendering layer's `@react-three/fiber` `<Canvas>` elements.
- Rename domain-level hooks and lib functions:
  - `src/lib/canvas.ts` -> `src/lib/design.ts`
- Move routing:
  - `src/app/[locale]/canvas` -> `src/app/[locale]/design`
  - `src/app/api/canvas/dictionaries` -> `src/app/api/design/dictionaries`
  - Partner routes: `src/app/[locale]/partner/[roleId]/canvas` -> `.../design`
- Rename domain components in `src/components/layout/canvas` to `src/components/layout/design` (e.g. `CanvasHeader` -> `DesignHeader`, `CanvasOnboarding` -> `DesignOnboarding`).

